show images

985
00:53:32,362 --> 00:53:34,355
of ice breaking from
the edge of the Arctic

986
00:53:34,356 --> 00:53:36,347
what they don't say is that...

987
00:53:36,348 --> 00:53:38,339
this is as ordinary event in the Arctic

988
00:53:38,340 --> 00:53:41,326
as falling leaves on
an English autumn day.

989
00:53:41,627 --> 00:53:45,312
They ask me, they just see ice falling

990
00:53:45,313 --> 00:53:47,303
from the edge of the greatest:

991
00:53:47,304 --> 00:53:52,284
yes, that's spring breakup
that happens every year.

992
00:53:52,285 --> 00:53:55,271
Press come to us towards
the time, you know:

993
00:53:55,272 --> 00:53:57,264
"you want to say something...

994
00:53:57,265 --> 00:54:00,253
...about the greenhouse disaster?",

995
00:54:00,254 --> 00:54:02,245
and I say: "there is none".

996
00:54:03,741 --> 00:54:05,731
Alarming television programs

997
00:54:05,732 --> 00:54:07,227
raised the fear for prospect

998
00:54:07,228 --> 00:54:09,718
a vast tidal waves flooding Britain.

999
00:54:09,719 --> 00:54:11,710
But what causes the sea
level to change...

1000
00:54:11,711 --> 00:54:13,702
...and how fast does it happen?

1001
00:54:14,199 --> 00:54:16,888
Sea level changes over
the world in general

1002
00:54:16,889 --> 00:54:19,876
are governed fundamentally
by two factors:

1003
00:54:19,877 --> 00:54:21,869
what we would call
"local factors",

1004
00:54:21,870 --> 00:54:23,562
the relationship of
the sea to the land

1005
00:54:23,563 --> 00:54:24,559
which often by the way is

1006
00:54:24,560 --> 00:54:26,053
to do with the land rising or falling

1007
00:54:26,054 --> 00:54:28,046
and anything to do with the sea,

1008
00:54:28,047 --> 00:54:29,043
but if you're talking about

1009
00:54:29,044 --> 00:54:32,030
what we call eustatic changes of sea,

1010
00:54:32,031 --> 00:54:34,022
worldwide changes of sea,

1011
00:54:34,023 --> 00:54:38,006
that's through the thermal
expansion of the oceans,

1012
00:54:38,007 --> 00:54:39,503
nothing to do with melting ice.

1013
00:54:39,504 --> 00:54:41,494
And that's an enormously slow,

1014
00:54:41,495 --> 00:54:42,490
a long process.

1015
00:54:44,980 --> 00:54:46,971
People say: "Oh, I see the ocean...

1016
00:54:46,972 --> 00:54:48,963
doing this last year...

1017
00:54:48,964 --> 00:54:51,952
that means that something changed

1018
00:54:51,953 --> 00:54:53,945
in the atmosphere last year",

1019
00:54:53,946 --> 00:54:55,935
and this is not
necessarily true at all,

1020
00:54:55,936 --> 00:54:57,928
in fact this is actually
quite unlikely

1021
00:54:57,929 --> 00:55:00,916
because it can take hundreds
to thousand of years

1022
00:55:00,917 --> 00:55:04,901
for the deep ocean to
respond to forces

1023
00:55:04,902 --> 00:55:05,897
and changes

1024
00:55:05,898 --> 00:55:07,889
hat are taking place
at the surface.

1025
00:55:08,886 --> 00:55:10,877
It is also suggested that

1026
00:55:10,878 --> 00:55:12,870
even a mild rise in temperature

1027
00:55:12,871 --> 00:55:15,112
will lead to the spread northward

1028
00:55:15,113 --> 00:55:18,599
of deadly insect-born tropical
diseases like malaria.

1029
00:55:18,945 --> 00:55:20,935
But is this true?

1030
00:55:22,429 --> 00:55:22,927
Professor Paul Reiter

1031
00:55:22,928 --> 00:55:24,920
of the Pasteur Institute in Paris

1032
00:55:24,921 --> 00:55:26,913
is recognized as one of the world's

1033
00:55:26,914 --> 00:55:28,605
leading experts on malaria

1034
00:55:28,606 --> 00:55:30,598
and other insect-born diseases.

1035
00:55:30,599 --> 00:55:32,589
He is a member of the
World Health Organization,

1036
00:55:32,590 --> 00:55:34,582
expert advisory committee...

1037
00:55:34,583 --> 00:55:35,578
was chairman of the...

1038
00:55:35,579 --> 00:55:37,571
American Committee
of Medical Entomology...

1039
00:55:37,572 --> 00:55:39,562
of the American Society
for Tropical Medicine...

1040
00:55:39,563 --> 00:55:41,555
and lead author on
the health section...

1041
00:55:41,556 --> 00:55:43,547
of the US National
Assessment...

1042
00:55:43,548 --> 00:55:47,034
of the potential consequences
of climate variability.

1043
00:55:49,027 --> 00:55:51,018
As Professor Reiter
is eager to point out,

1044
00:55:51,019 --> 00:55:55,003
mosquitoes thrive in
very cold temperatures.

1045
00:55:56,000 --> 00:55:58,987
Mosquitoes are not
specifically tropical.

1046
00:55:58,988 --> 00:55:59,984
Most people would
realize that...

1047
00:55:59,985 --> 00:56:02,474
in temper regions there
are mosquitoes;

1048
00:56:02,475 --> 00:56:04,466
in fact, mosquitoes are

1049
00:56:04,467 --> 00:56:06,458
extremely abundant
in the Arctic.

1050
00:56:07,457 --> 00:56:10,443
The most devastating
epidemic of malaria...

1051
00:56:10,444 --> 00:56:13,431
was in the Soviet
Union in the 1920's:

1052
00:56:13,432 --> 00:56:16,419
there was something like
13 million cases a year

1053
00:56:16,420 --> 00:56:19,408
and something like
600,000 deaths,

1054
00:56:19,409 --> 00:56:21,401
a tremendous
catastrophy...

1055
00:56:21,402 --> 00:56:23,391
that raised up to
the Arctic Circle...

1056
00:56:23,392 --> 00:56:26,379
Archangel had
13 thousand cases...

1057
00:56:26,380 --> 00:56:28,372
and about 10 thousand deaths.

1058
00:56:28,373 --> 00:56:30,365
So it's not a
tropical disease.

1059
00:56:30,366 --> 00:56:34,348
Yet these people in the
global warming fraternity

1060
00:56:34,349 --> 00:56:36,341
invent the idea that...

1061
00:56:36,342 --> 00:56:38,332
malaria will move northward.

1062
00:56:39,128 --> 00:56:41,321
Climate scare stories cannot be blamed

1063
00:56:41,322 --> 00:56:43,314
solely on sloppy or
biased journalism.

1064
00:56:43,315 --> 00:56:45,306
According to Professor Reiter,

1065
00:56:45,307 --> 00:56:47,297
hysterical alarms have
been encouraged...

1066
00:56:47,298 --> 00:56:53,275
by the reports of the UN's IPCC.

1067
00:56:53,276 --> 00:56:54,271
On spread of malaria,

1068
00:56:54,272 --> 00:56:56,263
the IPCC warns us that:

1069
00:56:56,264 --> 00:56:58,953
"Mosquito species that
transmit malaria...

1070
00:56:58,954 --> 00:56:59,949
do not usually survive...

1071
00:56:59,950 --> 00:57:01,445
where the mean
winter temperature...

1072
00:57:01,446 --> 00:57:04,434
drops below 16-18C".

1073
00:57:05,229 --> 00:57:06,822
According to Professor Reiter

1074
00:57:06,823 --> 00:57:08,814
this is clearly untrue.

1075
00:57:08,815 --> 00:57:10,806
I was horrified to read the second

1076
00:57:10,807 --> 00:57:12,798
and the third assessment reports

1077
00:57:12,799 --> 00:57:15,787
because there was
so much misinformation,

1078
00:57:15,788 --> 00:57:18,775
without any kind of records

1079
00:57:18,776 --> 00:57:22,759
or virtually without mention
of the scientific literature,

1080
00:57:22,760 --> 00:57:24,751
the trully scientific literature,

1081
00:57:24,752 --> 00:57:27,739
literature by specialists
in those fields.

1082
00:57:27,936 --> 00:57:29,928
In a letter to the
Wall Street Journal,

1083
00:57:29,929 --> 00:57:31,422
Professor Frederick Seitz,

1084
00:57:31,423 --> 00:57:34,411
America's National
Academy of Sciences,

1085
00:57:34,412 --> 00:57:36,404
revealed that IPCC officials

1086
00:57:36,405 --> 00:57:39,391
had censored the
comments of scientists.

1087
00:57:39,392 --> 00:57:40,388
He said that:

1088
00:57:40,389 --> 00:57:42,379
"This report is not
the version...

1089
00:57:42,380 --> 00:57:45,368
that was approved by
the contributing scientists"

1090
00:57:45,369 --> 00:57:48,357
At least 15 key sections
of the science chapter

1091
00:57:48,358 --> 00:57:49,352
...had been deleted.

1092
00:57:49,353 --> 00:57:51,344
These included statements like:

1093
00:57:51,345 --> 00:57:54,332
"None of the studies cited
has shown clear evidence...

1094
00:57:54,333 --> 00:57:56,325
...that we can attribute
climate changes...

1095
00:57:56,326 --> 00:57:58,318
...to increases in
greenhouse gases."

1096
00:57:58,319 --> 00:58:01,306
"No study to date has
positively attributed...

1097
00:58:01,307 --> 00:58:03,297
...all or part
of the observed

1098
00:58:03,298 --> 00:58:05,289
climate changes to
man-made causes."

1099
00:58:05,290 --> 00:58:07,282
Professor Seitz concluded:

1100
00:58:07,283 --> 00:58:11,266
"I have never witnessed
a more disturbing corruption

1101
00:58:11,267 --> 00:58:13,259
of the peer-review process

1102
00:58:13,260 --> 00:58:16,246
than the events that
led to this IPCC report."

1103
00:58:17,243 --> 00:58:18,737
In its reply, the IPCC...

1104
00:58:18,738 --> 00:58:21,228
did not deny making
these deletions;

1105
00:58:21,229 --> 00:58:23,219
but it said that there
was no dishonesty...

1106
00:58:23,220 --> 00:58:24,216
or bias in the report,

1107
00:58:24,217 --> 00:58:25,710
and that uncertainties about...

1108
00:58:25,711 --> 00:58:28,698
...the cause of global warming
had been included.

1109
00:58:28,699 --> 00:58:30,691
The changes have been made,

1110
00:58:30,692 --> 00:58:32,683
it said, in response
to comments...

1111
00:58:32,684 --> 00:58:34,675
...from governments,
individual scientists

1112
00:58:34,676 --> 00:58:36,667
and non-governmental
organizations.

1113
00:58:36,668 --> 00:58:39,655
When I resigned from the IPCC

1114
00:58:39,656 --> 00:58:41,648
I thought this was the end of it;

1115
00:58:41,649 --> 00:58:43,640
but when I saw the final draft,

1116
00:58:43,641 --> 00:58:45,632
my name was still there.

1117
00:58:45,633 --> 00:58:47,624
I asked for it to be removed:

1118
00:58:47,625 --> 00:58:48,620
Well, they told me,

1119
00:58:48,621 --> 00:58:51,607
that I had contributed
so it'd remain there.

1120
00:58:51,608 --> 00:58:53,601
So I said: "No, I haven't contributed

1121
00:58:53,602 --> 00:58:55,592
because they haven't
listened to anything I said".

1122
00:58:55,593 --> 00:58:57,585
So in the end it was
quite a battle

1123
00:58:57,586 --> 00:59:00,573
but finally I threatened
legal actions against them

1124
00:59:00,574 --> 00:59:01,569
and they removed my name,

1125
00:59:01,570 --> 00:59:03,562
and I think this happens
a great deal;

1126
00:59:03,563 --> 00:59:05,553
those people who are specialists

1127
00:59:05,554 --> 00:59:08,542
but don't agree
with the polemic

1128
00:59:08,543 --> 00:59:09,537
and resigned...

1129
00:59:09,538 --> 00:59:12,526
(and there have been
a number that I know of)

1130
00:59:12,527 --> 00:59:14,519
they are simply put
on the author list...

1131
00:59:14,520 --> 00:59:15,515
and become part of these...

1132
00:59:15,516 --> 00:59:18,005
2,500 of the world's
top scientists.

1133
00:59:18,999 --> 00:59:20,990
Research relating to
man-made global warming

1134
00:59:20,991 --> 00:59:23,978
is now one of the best
funded areas of science.

1135
00:59:23,979 --> 00:59:25,475
The US government alone spends...

1136
00:59:25,476 --> 00:59:27,466
...for than 4 billion dollars a year.

1137
00:59:27,964 --> 00:59:30,453
According to NASA
climatologist Roy Spencer,

1138
00:59:30,454 --> 00:59:31,450
scientists who speak out...

1139
00:59:31,451 --> 00:59:33,442
...against man-made global warming

1140
00:59:33,443 --> 00:59:35,434
have a lot to lose.

1141
00:59:35,435 --> 00:59:38,423
It's generally harder to get
research proposals funded

1142
00:59:38,424 --> 00:59:41,411
because of the stands
we've taken publicly,

1143
00:59:41,412 --> 00:59:42,406
and you'll find very few of us

1144
00:59:42,407 --> 00:59:44,399
that are willing to take public stand

1145
00:59:44,400 --> 00:59:47,388
because it does cut
into the research funding.

1146
00:59:47,886 --> 00:59:48,882
It is a common prejudice

1147
00:59:48,883 --> 00:59:51,373
that scientists
who do not agree...

1148
00:59:51,374 --> 00:59:53,364
with the theory of man-made
global warming...

1149
00:59:53,365 --> 00:59:56,352
must have been paid by
private industry to tell lies.

1150
00:59:56,848 --> 00:59:58,345
I get it all the time:

1151
00:59:58,346 --> 01:00:00,836
"You must be in the pay
of the multinationals".

1152
01:00:00,837 --> 01:00:03,824
Sadly, like most of the
scientists you'll talk to,

1153
01:00:03,825 --> 01:00:05,816
I haven't see a penny
from the multinationals.

1154
01:00:05,817 --> 01:00:07,310
I'm always accused of being paid

1155
01:00:07,311 --> 01:00:08,306
by oil and gas companies.

1156
01:00:08,307 --> 01:00:09,304
I've never received a nickel

1157
01:00:09,305 --> 01:00:11,295
from the oil and gas companies.

1158
01:00:11,296 --> 01:00:12,789
I joke about I wished
they would pay me

1159
01:00:12,790 --> 01:00:14,484
then I could afford
their product.

1160
01:00:14,485 --> 01:00:15,978
Whenever anybody says that...

1161
01:00:15,979 --> 01:00:18,965
I'm in the pay of an oil company,

1162
01:00:18,966 --> 01:00:20,959
I say my bank manager
would wish.

1163
01:00:23,446 --> 01:00:26,935
There's almost no private sector
investment in climatology

1164
01:00:26,936 --> 01:00:29,923
and yet, to be involved
in any reseach project

1165
01:00:29,924 --> 01:00:31,418
which involves an industry grant,

1166
01:00:31,419 --> 01:00:32,415
no matter how small,

1167
01:00:32,416 --> 01:00:35,403
and spell ruin to a
scientist's reputation.

1168
01:00:35,404 --> 01:00:38,391
Modern technology fuelled
by greenhouse gases.

