01:03:55,528 --> 01:03:57,019
but it gets pretty difficult

1241
01:03:57,020 --> 01:04:00,009
and pretty nasty and very personal.

1242
01:04:00,010 --> 01:04:03,992
And I've been death threats
and all sort of things

1243
01:04:03,993 --> 01:04:05,985
so I'm not doing it for my health.

1244
01:04:06,981 --> 01:04:08,973
These days, if you are skeptical

1245
01:04:08,974 --> 01:04:11,962
about the Litany around
climate change,

1246
01:04:11,963 --> 01:04:15,945
you are suddlely like as if
you are a Holocaust denier.

1247
01:04:17,439 --> 01:04:18,933
The environmental movement really

1248
01:04:18,934 --> 01:04:21,922
it is a political activist movement

1249
01:04:21,923 --> 01:04:25,906
and they have become hugely
influential at a global level.

1250
01:04:29,592 --> 01:04:32,083
And every politician
is aware of that today.

1251
01:04:32,631 --> 01:04:33,626
Whether you are in the left,

1252
01:04:33,627 --> 01:04:34,672
in the middle or the right,

1253
01:04:34,673 --> 01:04:38,159
you have to pay homage
to the environment.

1254
01:04:39,354 --> 01:04:40,347
In the past month,

1255
01:04:40,348 --> 01:04:41,843
the global warming campaign

1256
01:04:41,844 --> 01:04:42,839
has won a great victory:

1257
01:04:42,840 --> 01:04:44,832
the United States government,

1258
01:04:44,833 --> 01:04:46,825
once a bastion of resistance,

1259
01:04:46,826 --> 01:04:47,820
has succumbed.

1260
01:04:47,821 --> 01:04:50,312
George Bush is now an allied.

1261
01:04:50,808 --> 01:04:52,303
Western governments have now

1262
01:04:52,304 --> 01:04:54,295
embraced the need for
international agreements

1263
01:04:54,296 --> 01:04:56,288
to restrain industrial production

1264
01:04:56,289 --> 01:04:58,280
in the developed and developing world.

1265
01:04:59,773 --> 01:05:01,764
But is it what cost?

1266
01:05:01,765 --> 01:05:03,756
Paul Driessen is a former
environmental campaigner.

1267
01:05:04,754 --> 01:05:07,741
My big concern with
global warming,

1268
01:05:07,742 --> 01:05:10,729
is that the policies
being pushed...

1269
01:05:10,730 --> 01:05:13,717
to supposedly prevent
global warming...

1270
01:05:13,718 --> 01:05:16,706
are having a disastrous effect

1271
01:05:16,707 --> 01:05:18,698
...on the world's poorest people.

1272
01:05:18,699 --> 01:05:20,689
Global warming campaigners say

1273
01:05:20,690 --> 01:05:22,682
it does not harm to be on the safe side;

1274
01:05:22,683 --> 01:05:24,674
even if the theory of man-made

1275
01:05:24,675 --> 01:05:25,670
climate change is wrong,

1276
01:05:25,671 --> 01:05:27,663
we should impose draconian measures

1277
01:05:27,664 --> 01:05:30,650
to cut carbon emissions, just in case.

1278
01:05:31,150 --> 01:05:34,137
They call this the
precautionary principle.

1279
01:05:34,635 --> 01:05:37,623
The precautionary principles
are very interesting beast.

1280
01:05:37,624 --> 01:05:39,616
It's basically used to promote

1281
01:05:39,617 --> 01:05:41,607
a particular agenda in ideology,

1282
01:05:41,608 --> 01:05:44,595
it's always used in one direction only.

1283
01:05:44,596 --> 01:05:48,580
It talks about the risks of
using a particular technology

1284
01:05:48,581 --> 01:05:50,573
fossil fuels for example,

1285
01:05:50,574 --> 01:05:53,561
but never about the
risks of not using it.

1286
01:05:53,562 --> 01:05:55,552
It never talks about the benefits

1287
01:05:55,553 --> 01:05:57,544
of having that technology.

1288
01:05:59,537 --> 01:06:01,032
Anne Mougela is about to cook...

1289
01:06:01,033 --> 01:06:03,025
...a meal for her children.

1290
01:06:03,026 --> 01:06:05,016
She is one of the 2 billion people,

1291
01:06:05,017 --> 01:06:07,008
a third of the world's population,

1292
01:06:07,009 --> 01:06:09,000
who have no access to electricity.

1293
01:06:09,001 --> 01:06:10,992
Instead, they must burn wood

1294
01:06:10,993 --> 01:06:12,985
or dried animal dung in their homes.

1295
01:06:13,983 --> 01:06:15,973
The indoor smoke this creates

1296
01:06:15,974 --> 01:06:18,961
is the deadliest form of
pollution in the world.

1297
01:06:18,962 --> 01:06:20,953
According to the World
Health Organization,

1298
01:06:20,954 --> 01:06:23,445
four million children
under the age of five...

1299
01:06:23,446 --> 01:06:25,934
die each year from
respiratory diseases...

1300
01:06:25,935 --> 01:06:27,926
caused by indoor smoke,

1301
01:06:27,927 --> 01:06:29,918
and many millions of
women die early...

1302
01:06:29,919 --> 01:06:32,408
from cancer and lung disease
for the same reason.

1303
01:06:33,404 --> 01:06:36,890
If you ask a rural person
to define development,

1304
01:06:36,891 --> 01:06:38,384
they'll tell you:

1305
01:06:38,385 --> 01:06:40,875
"yes I'll know I move
to the next level

1306
01:06:40,876 --> 01:06:42,370
when I have electricity".

1307
01:06:42,868 --> 01:06:44,363
Actually not having electricity

1308
01:06:44,364 --> 01:06:46,851
creates such a long
chain of problems...

1309
01:06:46,852 --> 01:06:49,591
cause the first thing
you miss is the light.

1310
01:06:49,592 --> 01:06:52,331
So you have to go to sleep earlier

1311
01:06:52,332 --> 01:06:54,322
because there's no light,

1312
01:06:54,323 --> 01:06:56,316
there's no reason to
stay awake, I mean,

1313
01:06:56,317 --> 01:06:59,303
you can't talk to each
other in darkness.

1314
01:06:59,304 --> 01:07:01,295
No refrigeration or
modern packaging...

1315
01:07:01,296 --> 01:07:03,287
means food cannot
be kept.

1316
01:07:03,288 --> 01:07:05,279
Fire in the hut is too smoky

1317
01:07:05,280 --> 01:07:08,269
and consumes too much
wood to be used as heating.

1318
01:07:08,766 --> 01:07:10,757
There is no hot water.

1319
01:07:10,758 --> 01:07:12,749
We in the West cannot
begin to imagine

1320
01:07:12,750 --> 01:07:15,241
how hard life is
without electricity.

1321
01:07:16,237 --> 01:07:17,483
The life expectancy of people...

1322
01:07:17,484 --> 01:07:20,219
who live like this in
terrifyingly short.

1323
01:07:20,220 --> 01:07:23,206
Their existance impoverished
in every way.

1324
01:07:26,196 --> 01:07:27,191
A few miles away the UN

1325
01:07:27,192 --> 01:07:29,684
is hosting its conference
on global warming

1326
01:07:29,685 --> 01:07:31,675
in its plush gated headquarters.

1327
01:07:33,668 --> 01:07:36,157
Gift shop is selling souvenirs
of peasant travel life

1328
01:07:36,158 --> 01:07:37,651
while delegates discuss...

1329
01:07:37,652 --> 01:07:39,646
how to promote what
are described as:

1330
01:07:39,647 --> 01:07:42,134
"sustainable forms of
electrical generation".

1331
01:07:44,128 --> 01:07:48,110
Africa has coal,
and Africa has oil,

1332
01:07:48,111 --> 01:07:50,104
but environmental groups
are campaigning...

1333
01:07:50,105 --> 01:07:52,096
against the use of these
sources of energy.

1334
01:07:54,089 --> 01:07:56,080
Instead, they say Africa...

1335
01:07:56,081 --> 01:07:58,072
and the rest of the
developing world...

1336
01:07:58,073 --> 01:08:00,063
...should use solar
and wind power.

1337
01:08:04,049 --> 01:08:06,041
A short drive out of Nairobi

1338
01:08:06,042 --> 01:08:08,033
we find our first solar panel.

1339
01:08:09,527 --> 01:08:11,519
A Kenian public health official

1340
01:08:11,520 --> 01:08:13,013
has brought us to a clinic

1341
01:08:13,014 --> 01:08:15,005
which serves several villages.

1342
01:08:16,002 --> 01:08:17,497
The only electrical
implements...

1343
01:08:17,498 --> 01:08:19,986
in the clinic are
the electric lights...

1344
01:08:19,987 --> 01:08:21,978
and a refrigerator in which
to keep vaccines,

1345
01:08:21,979 --> 01:08:24,469
medicine and blood samples.

1346
01:08:24,967 --> 01:08:27,955
Electricity is provided
by two solar panels.

1347
01:08:28,951 --> 01:08:33,932
- So what can you to do successfully?
- Lighting.

1348
01:08:33,933 --> 01:08:37,915
What happens when you put
lighting plus the refrigerator?

1349
01:08:37,916 --> 01:08:39,907
Tell us, what happens?

1350
01:08:39,908 --> 01:08:43,392
- It sounds an alarm?
- Yes.

1351
01:08:43,393 --> 01:08:46,382
- Can we maybe see that?

1352
01:08:53,354 --> 01:08:56,342
The solar panels allow Dr. Samuel Morangui

1353
01:08:56,343 --> 01:08:59,330
to use either the lights
or the refrigerator,

1354
01:08:59,331 --> 01:09:01,322
but not both at
the same time.

1355
01:09:01,323 --> 01:09:04,310
If he does, the
electricity shuts down.

1356
01:09:05,805 --> 01:09:08,793
Wind and solar power
are notoriously unreliable

1357
01:09:08,794 --> 01:09:09,789
as a source of electricity,

1358
01:09:09,790 --> 01:09:12,777
and are at least three
times more expensive

1359
01:09:12,778 --> 01:09:15,764
than conventional forms
of electrical generation.

1360
01:09:16,761 --> 01:09:19,749
The question would be
how many people in Europe,

1361
01:09:19,750 --> 01:09:21,742
how many people in the United States

1362
01:09:21,743 --> 01:09:24,233
are already using
that kind of energy,

1363
01:09:24,234 --> 01:09:26,721
and how cheap is it, you see,

1364
01:09:26,722 --> 01:09:29,212
if it's expensive for the Europeans,

1365
01:09:29,213 --> 01:09:31,203
if it's expensive for the Americans,

1366
01:09:31,204 --> 01:09:33,695
and we are talking
about poor Africans,

1367
01:09:33,696 --> 01:09:36,186
you know, it doesn't make sense.

1368
01:09:36,187 --> 01:09:38,178
The rich countries
can afford...

1369
01:09:38,179 --> 01:09:39,673
to engage in some
luxurious

1370
01:09:39,674 --> 01:09:42,661
experimentation with
other forms of energy,

1371
01:09:42,662 --> 01:09:44,903
but for us we are still
at the state of survival.

1372
01:09:47,640 --> 01:09:49,631
To former environmentalist
Paul Driessen,

1373
01:09:49,632 --> 01:09:52,619
the idea that the world's
poorest people

1374
01:09:52,620 --> 01:09:54,611
should be restricted
to using the world's

1375
01:09:54,612 --> 01:09:58,596
most expensive and inefficient
forms of electrical generation,

1376
01:09:58,597 --> 01:10:01,087
is the most morally
repugnant aspect...

1377
01:10:01,088 --> 01:10:03,079
of the global warming campaign.

1378
01:10:04,574 --> 01:10:07,560
Let me make one
thing perfectly clear:

1379
01:10:07,561 --> 01:10:09,552
if we are telling the Third World

1380
01:10:09,553 --> 01:10:12,541
that they can only have
wind and solar power,

1381
01:10:12,542 --> 01:10:15,032
what we are really telling them is:

1382
01:10:15,033 --> 01:10:17,522
"You cannot have electricity".

1383
01:10:19,017 --> 01:10:20,511
The challenge we have,

1384
01:10:20,512 --> 01:10:23,499
when we meet western
environmentalists

1385
01:10:23,500 --> 01:10:25,492
who say we must engage

1386
01:10:25,493 --> 01:10:29,475
in the use of solar panels
and wind energy

1387
01:10:29,476 --> 01:10:32,463
is how we can have
Africa industrialized,

1388
01:10:33,461 --> 01:10:36,449
because I don't see how a solar panel

1389
01:10:36,450 --> 01:10:39,437
is going to power a steel industry,

1390
01:10:39,438 --> 01:10:41,428
how a solar panel, you know,

1391
01:10:41,429 --> 01:10:46,410
is going to power maybe
some railway train network.

1392
01:10:47,406 --> 01:10:51,390
It might work maybe to
power a transistor radio.

1393
01:10:53,384 --> 01:10:55,373
I think one of the most pernicious aspects

1394
01:10:55,374 --> 01:10:57,366
of the modern environmental movement

1395
01:10:57,367 --> 01:11:00,355
is the romantization of peasant life,

1396
01:11:01,351 --> 01:11:04,339
and the idea that industrial societies

1397
01:11:04,340 --> 01:11:07,326
are the destroyers of the world.

1398
01:11:08,821 --> 01:11:10,813
One clear thing that emerges

1399
01:11:10,814 --> 01:11:13,303
from the old environmental debate

1400
01:11:13,304 --> 01:11:16,291
is the point that there's somebody

1401
01:11:16,292 --> 01:11:19,279
keen to kill the African dream,

1402
01:11:19,280 --> 01:11:21,272
and the African dream is to develop.

1403
01:11:21,521 --> 01:11:22,766
The environmental movement

1404
01:11:22,767 --> 01:11:26,053
has evolved into the
strongest force there is

1405
01:11:26,054 --> 01:11:30,536
for preventing development
in the developing countries.

1406
01:11:30,537 --> 01:11:32,529
We have been told
don't touch your resources,

1407
01:11:32,530 --> 01:11:33,525
don't touch your oil,

1408
01:11:33,526 --> 01:11:35,517
don't touch your coal,

1409
01:11:35,518 --> 01:11:37,012
that is suicide.

1410
01:11:37,013 --> 01:11:40,499
I think it's legitimate for me
to call them anti-human,

1411
01:11:40,500 --> 01:11:42,490
like OK, you don't have to think

1412
01:11:42,491 --> 01:11:46,474
humans are better than whales,

1413
01:11:46,475 --> 01:11:48,465
or better than owls,

1414
01:11:48,466 --> 01:11:50,957
or whatever if you don't
want to, right?

1415
01:11:50,958 --> 01:11:54,941
But surely it is not a good idea

1416
01:11:54,941 --> 01:11:57,430
to think of humans as sort of being scum,

1417
01:11:57,431 --> 01:12:00,418
you know, that is OK to have
hundreds of millions them

1418
01:12:00,419 --> 01:12:02,412
going blind or dead or whatever,

1419
01:12:02,413 --> 01:12:04,404
I just can't relate to that.

1420
01:12:05,401 --> 01:12:07,392
The theory of man-made
global warming

1421
01:12:07,393 --> 01:12:09,383
is now so firmly entrenched,

1422
01:12:09,384 --> 01:12:12,371
the voices of opposition
so effectively silenced,

1423
01:12:12,372 --> 01:12:14,364
it seems invincible,

1424
01:12:14,365 --> 01:12:16,856
untroubled by any
contrary evidence,

1425
01:12:16,857 --> 01:12:18,848
no matter how strong.

1426
01:12:18,849 --> 01:12:23,330
The global warming alarm
is now beyond reason.

1427
01:12:24,327 --> 01:12:25,820
There will be still people

1428
01:12:25,821 --> 01:12:28,808
who believe that this is
the end of the world

1429
01:12:28,809 --> 01:12:31,796
particularly when you
have, for example,

1430
01:12:31,797 --> 01:12:34,784
the chief scientist
of the UK,

1431
01:12:34,785 --> 01:12:37,276
telling people that by
the end of the century

1432
01:12:37,277 --> 01:12:39,765
the only habitable
place on the earth

1433
01:12:39,766 --> 01:12:41,758
will be the Antarctic.

1434
01:12:41,759 --> 01:12:44,746
And it may, humanity
may survive

1435
01:12:44,747 --> 01:12:46,737
thanks to some
breeding couples

1436
01:12:46,738 --> 01:12:48,730
who moved to
the Antarctic.

1437
01:12:48,731 --> 01:12:51,718
I mean this is hilarious.

1438
01:12:51,719 --> 01:12:56,699
It would be hilarious
actually if it weren't so sad.
